first enable ssh from raspi-config 
the type vi /etc/dhcpcd.config 
in static ip adress section uncaument the line 
static ip adress = 192.168.0.1 
then reboot the system 


the errors i faced: 
ssh pi@192.168.0.10
ssh: connect to host 192.168.0.10 port 22: Network is unreachabl


to connect to pi via ssh etherent cable you can run 

ssh pi@192.168.0.10
ssh pi@freeways-pi.local


this video hepd me : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MGDhMaWOBWs
---------------- new way ------------- 
on your computer network configuration ethernet set a manual 
set an ip (192.168.0.0,255.255.255.0 ) 
go to raspi-config: enable ssh 
method1: 
in the pi get the hostname using: 
hostname -I: this command will return an ip adress 
the connect using : ssh pi@ip_adress
method2: 
ssh pi@raspberrypi.local
